default7.2.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default 
defaultIn the cement sector 60% of direct emissions of carbon dioxide arise from the decomposition of limestone (process emissions). 
defaultTo address its climate change 
defaultresponsibilities 
defaultthe UK cement industry has developed a GHG Strategy for 2050
default. It outlines where Government support is need
defaulted
default.
default One of the principle technologies will be carbon capture and storage (CCS) which could address both process emissions and combustion emissions fr
defaultom cement manufacture. 
defaultOpportunities to develop CCS cannot be achieved on short term funding timelines. 
defaultThe UK should follow the example set by the Norwegian Government by funding a cement industry CCS pilot plant. The Norwegian example is the first of its
default kind and shows that the UK will be behind other countries in its low carbon development if the current absence of industrial low carbon support is not rectified.
